a.title: Table dbo.Author Authors of books in collection
AuthorId * int Unique identifier for a specific author
Referred by AuthorOnlinePresense ( AuthorId ) Referred by BookAuthor ( AuthorId )
FirstName * varchar(30) Author first name
LastName * varchar(60) Author Last name
MiddleName * varchar(30) Optional Author Middle name (IE Deanna K Dwyer)
DateCreated datetime default getdate() Date the record was added
Table dbo.AuthorOnlinePresense
AuthorOnlinePrecenseId * int Uniquely identifies an online precense record
AuthorId * int identifies the author
References Author ( AuthorId )
Sitename * varchar(20) Name of the site related to the author (IE Twitter, Facebook, official website, etc.)
URL * varchar(255) URL for the site
SiteIcon varchar(40) Location of the icon to use for the Site
DateCreated datetime default getdate() Date the record was added
Table dbo.Book Books in collection
BookId * int unique identifier for a specific publication of a book. For example, if you have teh first printing and second printing of a book, those would be 2 seperate entries.
Referred by BookAuthor ( BookId ) Referred by BookGenre ( BookId )
SeriesId int If not null, identifies teh series the book is part of
References BookSeries ( SeriesId -> BookSeriesId )
SeriesOrder tinyint Identifies the order the book falls in within the series
Title * varchar(200) title of the book
PublicationYear * smallint what year was the book published in
DateCreated datetime default getdate() Date the record was added
BookCoverImage varchar(255) file location of the book cover image
Table dbo.BookAuthor This table will link one or more authors to a book. This will handle collaborations such as Stephen King and Peter Straub's The Talisman
BookId * int Identifies the book
References Book ( BookId )
AuthorId * int Identifies the author
References Author ( AuthorId )
Table dbo.BookGenre Links Book to Genre(s)
BookId * int udentifies book for genre
References Book ( BookId )
GenreId * tinyint Identifies genre for the book
References Genre ( GenreId )
Table dbo.BookSeries
BookSeriesId * int Identifies a series within the system
Referred by Book ( SeriesId -> BookSeriesId )
SeriesName * varchar(100) Name of the book series
DateCreated datetime default getdate() Date the record was added
Table dbo.Genre Possible genres for the books
GenreId * tinyint Uniquely identifies a genre within the system
Referred by BookGenre ( GenreId )
GenreName * varchar(100) Name of the genre
DateCreated * date default getdate() Date the record was added
